inference:
Let $\mathbf{a}$ denote the vector $\overrightarrow{OA}$, etc.  Then
\[\mathbf{d} = \frac{2}{3} \mathbf{a} + \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{b},\]\[\mathbf{e} = \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{b} + \frac{2}{3} \mathbf{c},\]and
\[\mathbf{f} = \frac{2}{3} \mathbf{c} + \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{a}.\][asy]
unitsize(0.4 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F;

A = (0,0);
B = (9,6);
C = (6,12);
D = (2*A + B)/3;
E = (B + 2*C)/3;
F = (2*C + A)/3;

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(D--E--F--cycle);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, SE);
label("$C$", C, N);
label("$D$", D, S);
label("$E$", E, NE);
label("$F$", F, NW);
[/asy]

Then
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{e} - \mathbf{f} &= \left( \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{b} + \frac{2}{3} \mathbf{c} \right) - \left( \frac{2}{3} \mathbf{c} + \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{a} \right) \\
&= \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{b} - \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{a} - \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{c} \\
&= \frac{1}{3} (\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{a} - \mathbf{c}),
\end{align*}and
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{d} - \mathbf{f} &= \left( \frac{2}{3} \mathbf{a} + \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{b} \right) - \left( \frac{2}{3} \mathbf{c} + \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{a} \right) \\
&= \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{a} + \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{b} - \frac{2}{3} \mathbf{c} \\
&= \frac{1}{3} (\mathbf{a} + \mathbf{b} - 2 \mathbf{c}).
\end{align*}Thus, the area of triangle $DEF$ is
\[\frac{1}{2} \|(\mathbf{e} - \mathbf{f}) \times (\mathbf{d} - \mathbf{f})\| = \frac{1}{18} \|(\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{a} - \mathbf{c}) \times (\mathbf{a} + \mathbf{b} - 2 \mathbf{c})\|.\]Expanding the cross product, we get
\[(\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{a} - \mathbf{c}) \times (\mathbf{a} + \mathbf{b} - 2 \mathbf{c}) = -\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b} + 2 \mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{c}.\]The area of triangle $ABC$ is
\[\frac{1}{2} \|\mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c} + \mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}\|.\]Hence, the ratio of the area of triangle $DEF$ to the area of triangle $ABC$ is
\[\frac{\frac{1}{18} \|-\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b} + 2 \mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{c}\|}{\frac{1}{2} \|\mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c} + \mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}\|} = \boxed{\frac{1}{9}}.\]

ground_truth:
First observe that if one vertex of a triangle is moved directly toward another vertex so as to shrink one side length of the triangle by a factor of $k$, then the area of the triangle is also shrinked by $k$.  To see this, think of the side that is shrinking as the base in the equation $\text{area}=\frac{1}{2}(\text{base})(\text{height})$.

Use brackets to denote area; for example, $[ABC]$ refers to the area of triangle $ABC$.  We have \[ [DBE]=\frac{1}{3}[DBC]=\frac{1}{3}\left(\frac{2}{3}[ABC]\right)=\frac{2}{9}[ABC]. \] Similarly, $[ADF]=[CFE]=\frac{2}{9}[ABC]$.  Therefore,  \begin{align*}
[DEF]&=[ABC]-[ADF]-[CFE]-[DBE] \\
&= \left(1-\frac{2}{9}-\frac{2}{9}-\frac{2}{9}\right)[ABC] \\
&=\frac{1}{3}[ABC],
\end{align*} so $[DEF]/[ABC]=\boxed{\frac{1}{3}}$.
[asy]
import graph;
size(150);
defaultpen(linewidth(0.7));
dotfactor=4;

xaxis(Ticks(" ",1.0,begin=false,end=false,NoZero,Size=3),Arrows(4));
yaxis(Ticks(" ",1.0,begin=false,end=false,NoZero,Size=3),Arrows(4));

pair A=(0,0), B=(9,6), C=(6,12), D=2*A/3+B/3, Ep=2*B/3+C/3, F=2*C/3+A/3;
pair[] dots={A,B,C,D,Ep,F};
Label[] alphabet={"$A$", "$B$", "$C$", shift(5,0)*"$D$", "$E$", "$F$"};
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(Ep--D--F--cycle);

int i;

for(i=0;i<=5;++i)

{

dot(alphabet[i],dots[i],unit(dots[i]-(A+B+C)/3));

}[/asy]

